description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an exciting opportunity within our Community Paediatrics department for an Assistant Medical Secretary - 18 hours per week. This is a fixed term post for a 6 month period from the beginning of December &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will need to enjoy a challenge and be used to working in a busy environment. You must be able to work on your own initiative and have excellent prioritisation, organisational and interpersonal skills. Some home working is required. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience of Microsoft Office packages is desirable together with experience in audio typing. The post holder will be expected to have good communication skills and be able to liaise effectively and efficiently with colleagues, professionals and patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information or an informal chat please contact Kate O’ Shea General Manager, Women and Children’s Directorate on 01432 355444 ext 5128 or email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Kate.oshea@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
